Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.72,0:44:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> you would have decisions to make\N>> right
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.56,0:44:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> this animal is sick and incurable. Shall\Nwe put it to sleep or not put it to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.40,0:44:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,sleep?\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.28,0:44:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Which is better? Yeah. Right. Like that.\NOkay. I see that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.40,0:44:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So each of those it comes up then.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.76,0:44:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Should we at this point alleviate the\Nsuffering or try to keep it going? So
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.83,0:44:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,each choice you see arises out of the\Nqualities that you have become yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.52,0:44:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as a human being.\NI was following a car one day and down
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.80,0:44:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the highway uh and uh the car actually\Nwent up on two wheels in its attempt to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.16,0:44:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,run over an animal. There was an animal\Nrunning in front of it, I forget, a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.11,0:45:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,squirrel or cat or whatever it was.\N>> And and this guy was so intent on
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.00,0:45:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,killing this animal, he actually went up\Non two wheels trying to get over to the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.28,0:45:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,side of the road to kill this animal.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.83,0:45:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> See?\NWell, thank you. Helps. Would you have
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.56,0:45:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,permission to take a picture?\N>> Yes. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.92,0:45:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> so\N>> the karma of that person, you know, just
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.80,0:45:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that intention, whether he killed it or\Nnot, I don't remember, but the intention
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.52,0:45:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I don't think he did kill it. I\Nthink but he I think I remember how it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.28,0:45:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,went now. It was so damn negative I\Nforgot it. He ran over the the animal
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.92,0:45:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and broke its neck. And the animal was\Nlying by the side of the road in a in
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.72,0:45:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,terrors of agony with a broken neck,\Ncurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.00,0:45:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And I had then to make the decision\Nwhether to bring its life to an end or
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.31,0:45:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,relieve its suffering or not.\N>> And you were making that that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.28,0:45:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I had to make the decision because I saw\Nthe squirrel or the rabbit, I forget
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.48,0:46:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which it was, with a broken neck laying\Nthere. Obviously irreparable damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.35,0:46:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But but often times we can get the\Nimpression that it wouldn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.64,0:46:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,mattered what choice you make from what\Nyou say. I mean this is where I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.44,0:46:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,confused like it doesn't matter what\Nchoice you make because it's not really
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.11,0:46:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you choosing anything. This is kind of\N>> but on the other hand it makes all the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.88,0:46:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,difference in the world.\N>> Yeah. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.88,0:46:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Simultaneously\N>> at the same time. Okay. I'll leave it at
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.72,0:46:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that. Thank you.\N>> Ambiguity spiritual work you learn to
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.48,0:46:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,tolerate ambiguity.\NIt both means everything and
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.11,0:46:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,simultaneously means nothing.\NThe world did not change.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.92,0:46:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.24,0:46:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hi. Nice to meet you.\NUm, today you called the physical world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.07,0:47:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What? Today you call the physical world\Nan illusion and a fairground
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.00,0:47:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and I understand it to be somewhere\Nwhere we have experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.56,0:47:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe to learn.\N>> I'm not understanding her.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.80,0:47:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> She said today you call the physical\Nworld
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.24,0:47:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> an illusion.\N>> Yeah. No, I don't call it an illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.04,0:47:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,though.\N>> Okay. I misunderstand
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.52,0:47:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> how you perceive it. How you perceive it\N>> is illusory but its existence is not
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.76,0:47:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,illusory. how you perceive it as kind or\Ncruel or
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.28,0:47:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> okay\N>> a disaster or a blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.52,0:47:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> or somewhere to experience\N>> how you perceive it is is is subjective
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.96,0:47:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\N>> my question is what's the point of our
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.16,0:47:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,physical reality and our physical bodies\Nif we all come from if we're all one
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.56,0:47:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we're all the name.\N>> Those are different levels of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.40,0:48:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,abstraction. You're mixing levels.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.00,0:48:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The oneness is that of context,\Nnot of physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.64,0:48:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The one emerging as the many.\NThe oneness of life emerges then through
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.04,0:48:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple expressions.\NThe whole animal kingdom, the vegetable
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.52,0:48:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,kingdom,\Nalthough they're multiple in their
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.40,0:48:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,physicality, they are one in the source\Nof life itself. The source of life is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.55,0:48:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,one in all living things. Yes. And yet\Nthe form form
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.83,0:48:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of multiplicity, diversity.\N>> So what's the point of the physical?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.76,0:48:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't have to have a point. What do\Nyou need a point for?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.00,0:48:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> To make meaning.\N>> What?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.07,0:48:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> To make meaning.\N>> To have meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.88,0:48:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Meaning.\N>> Don't give it any meaning. Had no
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.59,0:48:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.04,0:49:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Just is. The world is. That's good\Nenough.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.00,0:49:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. Thank you.\N>> The book I'm just finishing gives you an
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.55,0:49:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,option of about 35 different meanings\Nthat you can project onto the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.92,0:49:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks.\NThe world is a mad house. The world is a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.44,0:49:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,recuperation\Nward.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.96,0:49:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is a joke. The world is a\Ntragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.11,0:49:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is a perplexity.\NThe purpose of the world is salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.72,0:49:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is purgatorial.\NThe world is a comedy. The world is a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.24,0:49:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,sadness.\NWhat you make of the world is your own
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.48,0:49:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,projection.\N>> It's all of those things and none of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.20,0:50:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,them.\N>> Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.20,0:50:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. Um, I gave up uh giving to\Ncharity because I heard you say the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.35,0:50:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,world is perfect as it is. And\Nyet when I pass by the homeless people
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.68,0:50:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that I encounter frequently, um, I just\Npass them by, I feel like there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.83,0:50:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,stone here in my chest. So, I don't know\Nwhat that is. Maybe I'm just not at the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.52,0:50:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,level where I see the world\Num, perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.72,0:50:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's perception.\N>> You don't have to materialist
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.68,0:50:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or other\Ndonate food.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.52,0:50:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> But she's asking about meaning though.\NMeaning
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.48,0:50:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I understand she gave up giving. I don't\Nat all.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.20,0:51:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, you can give up giving.\NYou can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.20,0:51:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh,\N>> don't they have poor houses?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.92,0:51:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't they have workhouses for the poor?\N>> Get money from a hardworking man.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.00,0:51:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Scrooge. Yes.\N>> So, just give in other ways then.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.40,0:51:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,carrying this, you know,\N>> volunteer at the hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.00,0:51:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> you know,\Ngo in and at the children's hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.40,0:51:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,volunteer to read stories. There's lots\Nof things to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.80,0:51:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> okay?\N>> You know, it might require time, but it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.59,0:51:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't necessarily require anything\Nelse.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.96,0:52:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,write a check.\N>> Okay, sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.76,0:52:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Can I get a picture?\N>> Laugh at comedian's jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.40,0:52:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, those are all loving things you\Ncan do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.44,0:52:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.80,0:52:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a year since I've sat here\Nthat I've been able to be in this place
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.83,0:52:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and I just wanted to come and present\Nmyself to you and give great thanks for
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.40,0:53:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what you have offered. I've been\Nfortunate also to be able to watch your
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.24,0:53:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,videos and listen to your CDs throughout\Nthe year. So, um, being far away doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.52,0:53:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,mean I'm far away in spirit. And\Num
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.07,0:53:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess uh what I've I don't really have\Na question, but what I've come to is um
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.07,0:53:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it is only a matter of letting thy will\Nbe done.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.68,0:53:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And um\Nto do that in each moment
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.92,0:53:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,uh I'm not always very good at. I have\Nmy
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.92,0:53:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, don't make it a serial\N>> a serial series of of decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.80,0:53:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You make a blanket decision\Nwithout reservations.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.59,0:53:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you do that, you make decision\Nabout
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.24,0:54:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,how much variation you will allow\Nyourself
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.40,0:54:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you can live live with that\Ndecision. You only need to make one
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.00,0:54:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,decision.\NLet's say you make a decision to be as
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.04,0:54:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,loving towards all of life and all of\Nits expressions as you can. That's a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.92,0:54:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,blanket decision. Now you don't have to\Nmake a lot of little decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.04,0:54:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Just one.\N>> Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.83,0:54:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N>> Make one blanket one that covers them
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.92,0:54:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,all.\N>> Covers them all. Okay. Thank you,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.55,0:54:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,doctor.\NUm, Dr. Hawkins, I was um hoping you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.64,0:54:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,could say a few words about your\Nrelationship with Bill Wilson.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.55,0:54:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew Bill for years\Nand u worked with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.80,0:55:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We went on speaking together a couple\Ntimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.24,0:55:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We worked on u evolving treatments for\Nthe recovery of alcoholics.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.48,0:55:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The clinic I had in Manass, Long Island,\Nuh treated great many of maybe the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.83,0:55:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,majority of alcoholics\Non Long Island. And uh we specialized in
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.59,0:55:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult cases that weren't able to\Nrecover or get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.16,0:55:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh we had a certain routine that we\Ndid.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.83,0:55:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh many of them had functional\Nhypoglycemia. They stop drinking and
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.04,0:55:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,then they go in for hot fud Sundays and\Non Sunday they're very very depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.40,0:55:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Say the hell with it and go get drunk.\NSo sugar-free diets and high doses of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.16,0:55:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,vitamin B3\Nthey recovered by the hundreds. Frankly,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.52,0:55:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the they had been hopeless. Functional\Nhypoglycemia being probably the worst
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.00,0:55:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,one because you you your blood sugar\Nshoots way too high. You know, you used
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.04,0:55:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to get drunk every Saturday night. Now\NSaturday night you have a hot fud
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.59,0:56:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunday. So your blood sugar drops up\Nhigh like this then it skyrockets down.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.16,0:56:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's really a problem of\Nhyperinsulinism.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.16,0:56:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This input of glucose then precipitates\Nuh a release of insulin. The insulin
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.55,0:56:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,brings the blood sugar down rapidly. It\Ndoesn't come down slowly and stop at 110
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.68,0:56:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or something. It skyrockets\Ngets down and will get down to 70 or 60
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.52,0:56:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you start shaking.\NOkay. Have a hot fight Sunday for
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.11,0:56:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,breakfast and see how you feel. About\N1:00 in the afternoon, you'll notice
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.92,0:56:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,your hands are shaking. Your emotions\Nare brittle. You're willing to kill
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.00,0:56:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself, commit suicide, throw the\Nradio out the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.48,0:56:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,become irrational. Some people become\Nviolent. We have many patients who were
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.64,0:56:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,arrested over and over for unsolicited\Nviolence.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.96,0:56:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And all they all they had to do is stop\Neating sugar and sweets.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.44,0:56:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So when people call for an appointment,\NI say, "What's your problem?" I get
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.24,0:56:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,angry. I'll get depressed. I say, "Well,\NI want you to stop eating sugar and
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.88,0:57:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,sweets until I see you." And about half\Nthe time by and when I saw him for the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.59,0:57:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,first appointment, they would say, "You\Nknow what? It's gone already."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.79,0:57:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The most misdiagnosis\Nalso poo pooed by conventional doctors.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.11,0:57:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember a guy weighed 400 pounds.\NHe had sugar, a voracious appetite for
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.20,0:57:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sugar like you never saw. He would sit\Ndown at a table and he would be like,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.88,0:57:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,his eyes were like riveted. Anything\Nwith sugar in it. And uh I told him, I
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.72,0:57:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,forget what his prom was, being drunk, I\Nthink. Anyway, so I told him, you got to
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.76,0:57:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,stop sugar and sweets. Well, he\Nrecovered. Yes, he recovered. That's
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.35,0:57:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,right. He recovered and he was perfectly\Nfine. And uh then he went to see a lady
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.96,0:57:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,who was president of the uh some medical\Nsociety and alcoholism and she said,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.88,0:57:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, hi guys. See me a poo poo poo." She\Nsaid, "Poo poo poo." Of course, that's
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.92,0:58:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,what he was waiting for at 400 lb. He\Nwent right back into the sugar and
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.68,0:58:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,sweets and he was dead within months.\NGot drunk again. Dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.79,0:58:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So her disbelief cost him his life.\NWhen your blood sugar drops, you become
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.07,0:58:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,irrational. So many of these people you\Nsee commit senseless crimes. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.11,0:58:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,always looking for a motive. There isn't\Nany motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.64,0:58:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have any motive.\NThat which the Freud call, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.31,0:58:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud called the id, in the bottom of\Nthe id is all the negativity that's
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.48,0:58:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,possible. All you got to do is bring\Ndown a person's blood sugar far enough
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.64,0:58:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and the average person will become\Npsychotic, violent,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.11,0:58:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,shoot their schoolmates. Crazy as all\Nget out.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.07,0:59:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So yes, we worked on things like that.\NAnd uh so I got to love Bill you know
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.96,0:59:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh he was also into exploration of\Nvarious things you know and when he died
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.52,0:59:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I was one of the doctors that came in to\Nsee what we could do to increase
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.64,0:59:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,oxygenation in his brain and certain\Nthings that were good for it weren't
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.76,0:59:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,legal in the US so we bootleg them. So I\Nwould
